@startuml EnrollmentActivity
title Course enrollment workflow\n(UML activity — lab structure)

skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #FEF9E7
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #333333
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
' Do not use ConditionEndStyle hline here: with nested if + swimlanes it draws
' extra horizontal bars that look like a merge/sync line crossing into Admin.

|#E3F2FD|Student|
start
:Login;
:Validate User;
:Select Course;
:Check course availability;

if (Course available?) then (yes)
  :Submit Enrollment;

  |#E8F5E9|Administrator|
  :Admin Approval;

  ' Decision and outcomes stay in Student lane so the join merges only student paths,
  ' then one arrow to the final state (matches typical lab layout).
  |#E3F2FD|Student|
  if (Approved?) then (yes)
    :Confirm Enrollment;
  else (no)
    :Enrollment Rejected;
  endif

else (no)
  |#E3F2FD|Student|
  :Show Message;
endif

stop

legend right
  **Typical implementation**
  Login: authenticate user
  Validate User: session + role check for enrollment
  Check availability: profile, capacity, prerequisites, duplicates, course exists
  Submit: create pending enrollment request
  Admin Approval: approve or reject request
  Confirm / Rejected: final status + notify student
  Show Message: validation or business-rule error to user
endlegend

@enduml
